cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and specifically focuses on improving the performance of feature pyramid methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for fusing multi-scale feature maps using bidirectional long short term memory (biLSTM) and channel-wise attention model, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on object detection benchmarks, which could also place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
